venue.name: Love At First Bite (เลิฟแอทเฟิร์สไบท์)

tip.text: I had a bangers and mash. Bangers was a kurobuta sausages on a bed of fluffy mashed potatoes! Quite good.
The ever changing art on the walls.
Well.... Taste like every other burgers in Melbourne though. But this place is always crowded!
Still one of the best cafes in kl. and one of the best crab burgers.

formattedAddress: 50000 Kuala Lumpur City Center, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Really love the ambience here. Great music and coffee while I work on some stuff.

formattedAddress: 50000 Kuala Lumpur City Center, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Just a stone throw away from where I lived! Food is good. Coffee is good too! Staffs are friendly! What more could I ask for!
High glass windows. Lots of good natural lighting. Pretty minimal interior design. Like the facade, food and service is pleasing on the taste buds. Kitchen closes at 8pm though.
Parking is a little bit difficult to secure as usual. Part and parcel of Uptown. But their selection of affogato is quite impressive. The black Forrest affogato I had was quite good!
2 words. KAPITI ICE-CREAM!
Softest. Creamiest ice cream! Not sure which is better now. Cold stone or this.
Next door to Yeast. They share the same owner and sometimes even the same chefs. But I love this place cuz it's NON HALAL! Great brunch selection too!
Everything here is good. Value for money too! French pastries FTW!!
My fav craft beer bar in the whole of Klang Valley. No matter how busy and crowded they are, staffs and owners are still friendly. A very good place to fall in love with craft beers!
Kicks S.Wine right in the ball sack! It's not overpriced and not greasy at all. Best of all.... Not overrated
Coffee is good here. Nice ambiance and interior design. Slightly on the pricier side but taste good.
Wide varieties of unique tarts. Come before lunch and the entire counter top is filled with many different kind of pastries to choose from. I don't recommend their French toast though. Too soggy...

formattedAddress: No. 16 Jalan Medan Setia Dua (Plaza Damansara)

tip.text: Overpriced food with catchy names. Don't recommend having the Nutella coffee. I'm not pleased that the Nutella overpowers the coffee instead of complimenting it.
Coffee and desserts here are great! Give their chendol cake a try. It's something different.
A pair of scones for rm9. With this price, don't expect it to be Harrod's standard or even Nosh bangsar's.
Love the ambiance for this place. A little bit on the minimalistic interior design. Tiramisu (contains alcohol) was great!
Ordered Chicken Ceaser Salad and this is the first time I ate Ceaser Salad that was served with poached (?) egg. Not good at all. Mash potatoes are tasteless and starchy (I think they added flour?)
My usual poison would be cappuccino. I don't usually go for flat white (doesn't deliver the kick that I need) but I will make an exception for this place. Flat white was smooth and aromatic.

formattedAddress: Suite G06, Ground Floor, Lobby 2 Menara See Hoy Chan (374, Jalan Tun Razak)
location.address: Suite G06, Ground Floor, Lobby 2 Menara See Hoy Chan

tip.text: Austria in Chinatown. I only manage to try the sausages and it was the best i ever had. Hands down! I'll come back for others next time.

formattedAddress: 5 Banda St, #01-52 K88 Coffee House (Sago Lane)

tip.text: Came here 3 times. Only the 3rd time i manage to dine in. I suggest they add more tables to accommodate the breakie crowd. Prepare to wait to get a seat if you want to have brunch/bfast here.
This place have been my go to coffee place whenever im within the CBD area since ever. Cosy and serves good coffee. Good break from a stressful day.
Had the best Cappuccino ever! Smooth and aromatic. If I want to have this everyday, I have to drive 20+ km from my usuals. That's the only downside for me. Oh! And it's only rm8.90. So much win!
Staff were very friendly. I ordered their bacon pasta... It's very similar to 3little pigs bacon pasta. But the Green Goblin drink definitely knock my socks off.
Friendly people here. Burger was HUGE AF! Fries were bountiful. I will be back here often if I don't live 18km away...
Very underrated place in TTDI area. Desserts are cheap and delicious. Pastas are to die for as they are perfectly al dente. Best of all, NON HALAL!

formattedAddress: 7A, Lorong Rahim Kajai 13, Taman Tun Dr. Ismail 60000 Kuala Lumpur
location.address: 7A, Lorong Rahim Kajai 13, Taman Tun Dr. Ismail 60000 Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: I tried their duck confit and it was really tender. I don't even need the knife to cut the meat. Also love the service here. Waiters are attentive and friendly.

formattedAddress: Verve Shops, Jalan Kiara 5 (G-5, Ground Floor)

tip.text: The same people who runs The Three Little Pigs and The Big Bad Wolf in Bangsar Village. Same menu as well....
Didn't place any order during reservation. So we didn't have the chance to try their signature dishes. But we were there to Lou Sang. Best Lou Sang I've ever had so far!

venue.name: Restaurant Extra Super Tanker (文華軒大飯店)

tip.text: Savory crepes served with warm smiles. Accompanied with cosy chill out environment. Ordered a Shore To Please and pleased i was.
Best hokkien me in Uptown Area, in my opinion. It's not over crowded and overrated. And open until 2am.

venue.name: Restoran Tiong Hokkien Mee 新青山亚华

tip.text: They now serve afternoon tea! And set lunch! I must say the dessert here is just superb. Presentation and taste is all there. Hats off to the chef behind all the pastries and desserts.
Sous vide lamb shank is the bomb! Tender and succulent. The meat just falls right off the bones! I don't even know why they bother to give me a knife.
Love the cold brew here. Cakes and desserts are lovely

venue.name: Chye Seng Huat Hardware Coffee Bar

tip.text: Totally understand the hype about this place. Everything is good here. Lol
Nice-ish environment. But because it's a bus station and its situated in one of the busiest part of KL, noise pollution can't be avoided. But coffee is good though...

tip.text: Awesome place!!! Love the environment n food. Makes sarawak club and lok thian look and taste like shit!
